President Cyril Ramaphosa is expected to woo the thousands of delegates and potential investors and promote South Africa as an attractive investment destination. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa is addressing the Investing in African Mining Indaba in Cape Town on Tuesday. Ramaphosa and Mineral Resource Minister Gwede Mantashe are expected to woo the thousands of delegates and potential investors and promote South Africa as an attractive investment destination. WATCH LIVE: Ramaphosa addresses Mining Indaba 